queries.details: Information identifying the producing insurance agency responsible for the submission, including agency identity, contact details, and internal agency identifiers used for carrier processing and account tracking.

entities.criteria: Producing insurance agency name associated with the submission.
Complete agency mailing address, including street, city, state, and ZIP when available.
Internal account identifier used by the agency.
Primary agency contact person for this submission.
Primary phone number of the agency.
Fax number of the agency, if present.
Email address of the agency contact.
Carrier-assigned code identifying the agency.
Sub-agency or branch identifier under the main agency.

queries.details: Information that identifies the insurance carrier involved in the submission, including the carrier’s legal name and regulatory identifiers used to distinguish it from other insurers.

entities.criteria: Insurance carrier issuing or quoting the current policy.
NAIC identifier of the carrier for the current policy.

queries.details: Information that uniquely identifies the insurance policy or program associated with the submission, including carrier-specific policy names, numbers, underwriting ownership, and internal reference codes.

entities.criteria: Policy or program name of the current policy.
Internal code identifying the current policy or program.
Policy number of the current policy.
Underwriter assigned to the current policy.
Office or region of the assigned underwriter.
Transaction status of the submission; output one of: Quote, Issue, Renew, Change, Cancel.
Line of business being applied for in this submission; output Business Auto.

Names of all supplemental forms, schedules, or sections that are indicated as attached to the submission. These may include schedules related to property values, vehicles, drivers, additional interests, premises, specialty exposures, or coverage-specific supplements. Only include attachments that are explicitly shown as included; do not infer missing attachments.
Effective date of the current policy in MM/DD/YYYY format.
Expiration date of the current policy in MM/DD/YYYY format.
Billing structure for the current policy (Direct or Agency).
Installment or payment plan for the current policy.
Payment method used for the current policy.
Indicates whether the current policy is auditable; output Yes or No.
Deposit required to bind the current policy.
Minimum premium required by the carrier for the current policy.
Total premium for the current policy.

queries.details: Information identifying the primary insured entity applying for coverage, including legal identity, business classification, tax identifiers, and core contact details.

entities.criteria: Legal name of the first named insured on the current policy.
Mailing address of the first named insured.
Primary business phone number of the insured.
Website of the insured, if provided.
General Liability class code applicable to the insured’s operations.
SIC code describing the insured’s business operations.
NAICS code describing the insured’s business operations.
Tax identification number of the insured.

queries.details: Information listing individuals associated with the insured account who serve specific roles (e.g., accounting, claims, inspection), including their communication details.

entities.criteria: Role of the contact related to the insured account (e.g., Accounting, Inspection, Claims).
Name of the contact person for the insured account.
Primary phone number for the contact.
Secondary phone number for the contact, if present.
Primary email address for the contact.
Secondary email address for the contact, if present.

queries.details: Information describing the physical locations associated with the insured’s operations, including address details, occupancy characteristics, employee counts, operational use, and revenue attribution per location.

entities.criteria: Identifier for each insured location.
Identifier for each building within a location.
Street address of the insured location.
City of the insured location.
County of the insured location.
State of the insured location.
ZIP code of the insured location.
Indicates whether the location is inside or outside city limits.
Insured’s interest in the location; output Owner or Tenant.
Full-time employees working at the location.
Part-time employees working at the location.
Description of operations conducted at the location.
Annual gross revenue attributed to the location.
Square footage occupied by the insured at the location.
Square footage accessible to the public at the location.
Total square footage of the building at the location.

entities.entity: Any Area Leased to Others? Y/N
entities.criteria: Indicates whether any portion of the location is leased to others; output Yes or No.

queries.details: Information describing the insured’s overall business operations, including business type, operational start date, primary activities, and the distribution of work performed on-premises versus off-premises.

entities.criteria: Overall business category of the insured.
Date the insured business began operations.
Description of the insured’s primary business activities.

entities.entity: Retail Stores or Service Operations % of Total Sales
entities.criteria: Percentage of total sales derived from retail or service operations.
Percentage of on-premises installation, service, or repair work performed by the insured.

entities.entity: Off Premises Installation, Service or Repair Work %
entities.criteria: Percentage of installation, service, or repair work performed off premises.

queries.details: Information identifying third parties that have a legal, financial, or contractual interest in the policy, property, vehicles, or items insured, including how and where that interest applies.

entities.criteria: Type of additional interest related to the policy, location, or vehicle.
Legal name of the additional interested party.
Mailing address of the additional interested party.
Priority ranking of the additional interest.
Evidence issued for the additional interest (Certificate, Policy, Send Bill).
Item, vehicle, or location number to which the interest applies.
Location number associated with the interest.
Building number associated with the interest.
Vehicle identifier associated with the interest.
Loan or reference number associated with the interest.
Outstanding lien amount.
End date of the additional interest.
Reason the interest exists (e.g., Leaseback, Ownership).
Phone number of the interested party.
Fax number of the interested party.
Email address of the interested party.
Classification of the insured item tied to the interest.
Item reference tied to the interest.
Description of the insured item tied to the interest.

queries.details: Free-form information providing underwriting notes, special handling instructions, or processing guidance that does not fit into structured data fields.

entities.criteria: Free-text notes related to underwriting or policy processing.

queries.details: Historical information about previous insurance coverage held by the applicant, organized by policy year and line category, used to evaluate continuity of coverage and underwriting history.

entities.criteria: Insurance carrier that provided prior coverage.
Policy year of the prior coverage.
Coverage category of the prior policy; output one of: Property, Automobile, General Liability, Other.
Line of business covered by the prior policy (e.g., Business Auto).
Policy number of the prior coverage.
Effective date of the prior policy.
Expiration date of the prior policy.
Premium amount for the prior policy year.

queries.details: Information detailing prior insurance claims or losses associated with the applicant, including dates, descriptions, financial impact, and claim status, or confirmation that no losses exist.

entities.criteria: Indicates whether any automobile losses exist; output Yes or No.
Date the automobile loss occurred.
Date the claim was reported.
Line of business associated with the loss; output Automobile.
Description of the automobile loss or claim.
Amount paid for the loss.
Outstanding reserve amount.
Indicates whether subrogation was pursued; output Yes or No.
Claim status; output Open or Closed.

queries.details: Information confirming that the application has been reviewed, authorized, and attested to by the appropriate parties, including producer and applicant acknowledgements, required disclosures, signatures, licensing identifiers, and execution dates.

entities.criteria: Printed name of the producer as shown in the designated field.
State-issued producer license number associated with the producer; include state context if shown.
National Producer Number assigned to the producer, if provided.
Date on which the application was signed, in MM/DD/YYYY format.

queries.details: Questions and answers indicating the applicant’s corporate relationships and operational footprint. Capture explicit Q&A about whether the applicant is a subsidiary of another entity, has subsidiaries, has foreign operations/foreign product exposure, has other business ventures not covered, and whether the business has been placed in a trust.

entities.criteria: The question text (from the ACORD form) about corporate relationships and operations (subsidiary status, subsidiaries, foreign ops/exposure, other ventures, trust).
The answer corresponding to that question (capture as stated; e.g., Yes/No, checkmarks, Y/N, etc.).

queries.details: Questions and answers about safety program status and hazard/compliance exposures. Capture explicit Q&A about whether a formal safety program is in operation, exposure to flammables/explosives/chemicals, and any uncorrected fire or safety code violations.

entities.criteria: The question text about safety program, hazardous materials exposure (flammables/explosives/chemicals), and uncorrected fire/safety code violations.
The answer corresponding to that question (capture as stated).

queries.details: Questions and answers about current/prior insurance and underwriting outcomes. Capture explicit Q&A about any other insurance with this company, and whether any policy/coverage has been declined, cancelled, or non-renewed during the prior three years.

entities.criteria: The question text about other insurance with this company and decline/cancel/non-renew in the prior three years.
The answer corresponding to that question (capture as stated).

queries.details: Questions and answers about sensitive claim/loss allegations and legal/financial history. Capture explicit Q&A about (a) losses/claims relating to sexual abuse, discrimination, or negligent hiring; (b) indictment/conviction for fraud, bribery, or arson; (c) foreclosure, repossession, or bankruptcy in the last five years; and (d) judgment or lien in the last five years.

entities.criteria: The question text about sexual abuse/discrimination/negligent hiring losses or claims; fraud/bribery/arson indictment/conviction; foreclosure/repossession/bankruptcy (last 5 years); judgment/lien (last 5 years).
The answer corresponding to that question (capture as stated).

queries.details: Questions and answers about drone (UAS) ownership/operation and whether the applicant hires others to operate drones.

entities.criteria: The question text about whether the applicant owns/leases/operates drones and whether the applicant hires others to operate drones.
The answer corresponding to that question (capture as stated).
